definition: to hand over/to pass on sth/to gradually increase or decrease/progressively
to deliver/to carry/to give (as a present)/to present (with)/to see off/to send

sentences.english: A clerk has just delivered the token by a bicycle.
sentences.chinese: 站员以脚踏车递送路牌予司机员以争取时间。

sentences.english: The mailman delivers letters and parcels every morning.
sentences.chinese: 邮差每天早晨递送信件和包裹。

sentences.english: Conclusions Using nanoparticles as genic carrier have a wide developmental foreground.
sentences.chinese: 结论纳米颗粒作为基因递送载体具有广阔的发展前景。

sentences.english: Bulk pack in export cartons on pallets for delivery.
sentences.chinese: 大量要递送的在草铺上输出品硬纸盒的包裹。

sentences.english: The return of an ongoing absentee ballot as undeliverable .
sentences.chinese: 因邮局无法递送，缺席或邮寄选票被退回。

sentences.english: The concentrate delivery system employs a positive displacement pump.
sentences.chinese: 浓缩物递送系统采用正位移泵。

sentences.english: The postman delivered a special delivery letter.
sentences.chinese: 那位邮差递送限时专送函。

sentences.english: The tiffin walas of Mumbia have been running their operations for over 100 years.
sentences.chinese: 孟买的午餐递送生意已有100多年的历史。

sentences.english: Second-day products delivery of the jet planes makes the world become smaller and smaller.
sentences.chinese: 喷气式飞机的次日货物递送使世界变得越来越小。

sentences.english: When does the next mail leave?
sentences.chinese: 下批邮件什么时候递送？

sentences.english: I'm using this to make outgoing calls to deliver alarm messages.
sentences.chinese: 我曾经做过外呼来递送报警信息。

definition: to forward (a message, letter, article etc)
to pass on to sb/to carry and give to sb else
to put together an order and deliver it (i.e. 配貨|配货[pei4 huo4] and 送貨|送货[song4 huo4])/to deliver (goods)
to distribute/distribution/to assign (sb) to a job
to become more urgent/more rapid/urgent/to handle a matter urgently
to present/to give/to hand over/to hand in/to lay before
